                            <comment id="16195274" author="karlpauls" created="Fri, 6 Oct 2017 21:37:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Similar to the issue we fixed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-5649&quot; title=&quot;Refreshing a fragment causes the framework to be restarted&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FELIX-5649&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FELIX-5649&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; we should not return required hosts for any other namespace than HOST_NAMESPACE from PackageAdmin getHosts. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Right now, we do and that causes the framework to be listed as host for all fragments (in other words, it still &lt;em&gt;looks&lt;/em&gt; like we would refresh the framework if you refresh the fragment even so we actually don&apos;t do that anymore due to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-5649&quot; title=&quot;Refreshing a fragment causes the framework to be restarted&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FELIX-5649&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FELIX-5649&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16195277" author="karlpauls" created="Fri, 6 Oct 2017 21:38:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in r1811372.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
